title: Prabowo Subianto - Wikipedia
snippet: In 1996, Prabowo led Operation Mapenduma in the mountainous terrain of Papua. The goal of the operation was the release of 11 scientific researchers who had been taken hostage by the Free Papua Movement (OPM). The researchers were five Indonesians, four Britons, one Dutchman and his pregnant German wife.

title: Titiek Suharto - Wikipedia
